notes: This registry is the canonical source of truth for enabled mods, load ordering, dependency overrides, and conflict declarations.

mods.yml is treated as an import-only feed: on each initializer run, mods.yml is reconciled into this registry, then mods.yml may be rewritten/cleaned to contain only items that were not imported (or emptied if fully imported), depending on initializer policy.
Workshop items may contain multiple Mod IDs. The initializer should scan each downloaded workshop item for mod.info files to discover all provided Mod IDs.
If a required Mod ID is missing, SteamCMD can only install it if there is a known mapping to a Workshop ID. Maintain these mappings over time under overrides.modIdToWorkshopId.
Optional require alias mapping: use overrides.requireAliases to map legacy require names to canonical Mod IDs (example: {"truemusic":"TrueMoozic"}).
Optional manual load-order hint: set numeric priority on individual mod entries (mods[].mods[].priority). Higher priority loads earlier when dependencies do not require another order.
